fields.description:
We still receive dozens of questions from customers via SAC and AAC about installing plugins and other restricted functionality. An experienced AAC member outlined [a common scenario in detail|https://answers.atlassian.com/questions/42495/where-do-we-submit-suggestions-for-improvements-to-the-ondemand-faqs-ondemand-sign-up-trial] and had this to say:
{quote}
My point is that at no stage during the signup trail do you actually give a clear view of the restrictions with OnDemand and even when you visit the full documentation and are given an indication that there are some restrctions it's not clear what those restrictions are. I don't believe you're deliberately trying to be misleading, but something's not right if the same questions are cropping up again and again.
{quote}

We should look at ways to improve the docs and the sign-up process (probably the WTF team) to make the restrictions clearer so that we can avoid wasting customers' time and reduce the Support load.

JIRA's gadget whitelist needs to be updated, some of the gadgets (so far the GreenHopper Rapid View Wallboard gadget but probably others) give an error:

{quote}
Requests to https://jira.atlassian.com/s/en_UKsx8qk0/710/2/1.0.8-beta/_/download/batch/com.atlassian.jira.collector.plugin.jira-issue-collector-plugin:issuecollector/com.atlassian.jira.collector.plugin.jira-issue-collector-plugin:issuecollector.js are not allowed. See your administrator about configuring a whitelist entry for this destination (http://confluence.atlassian.com/x/KQfCDQ ).
{quote}

I assume this is for analytics for GreenHopper.
